</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
</font></code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">Sec. 10. </font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">Community integration. </font></code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">(a) Community-integrated living arrangements
shall be located so as to enable residents to participate in and be
integrated into their community or neighborhood.  The location of such
arrangements shall promote community integration of persons with mental
disabilities.</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">

</font></code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">(b) Beginning January 1, 1990, no Department of State government, as
defined in the Civil
Administrative Code of Illinois, shall place any person in or utilize any
services of a community-integrated living arrangement which is not
certified by an agency under this Act.</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
</font></code><br><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">(Source: P.A. 100-602, eff. 7-13-18.)</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
